strings:
<voice_0x01001164><se_def>Cash: So these are the doors.
All I have to do is open them, and my hands will be marked with the family crest.
<voice_0x01001165><se_def>Cash: OW!

<voice_0x01001166><se_def>Cash: It's as hot as a fire-brand!
How am I going to open this!?
<voice_0x01001167><se_high>Carrie: What's wrong, ‘big’ brother?

<voice_0x01001168><se_high>Carrie: That's just from touching it.
Don't you think you'll have a little trouble actually getting both doors open by yourself?
<voice_0x01001169><se_high>Carrie: Especially considering what a wuss you can be over a little paper cut.
<voice_0x0100116A><se_def>Cash: You got me, sis. What can I say? How about coming up here and opening it with me?

<voice_0x0100116B><se_high>Carrie: Fine by me, Cash. But is it really fine by you?
I mean, if I help you, the fortune's going to be split between the two of us.
<voice_0x0100116C><se_high>Carrie: I'm sure it'll give us plenty to fight over.
<voice_0x0100116D><se_def>Cash: Ah, what have I done...?

<voice_0x0100116E><se_def>Cash: But I'm a man of my word.
Come on. Join me.
We'll inherit the fortune together.

<voice_0x0100116F><se_high>Carrie: Nobody's forcing you to do this.
So no regrets after the fact, okay?
<voice_0x01001170><se_def>Cash: Just take your side.
<voice_0x01001171><se_high>Carrie: Here goes nothing.

<voice_0x01001172><se_high>Carrie: AAAARGH!!!
OW, OW, OW!
<voice_0x01001173><se_def>Cash: After all that big talk, you're giving up now?
<voice_0x01001174><se_high>Carrie: Who's giving up? I just want to get back home and put some ice on my hand!
<voice_0x01001175><se_def>Cash: Not until after we go in and have our audience with our ancestor...!

<voice_0x01001176><se_def>Cash: You should join us as well.
There may be more monsters inside.
<voice_0x01001177><se_high>Carrie: All I have to do is open these doors, and the family crest will be marked on my hands.
<voice_0x01001178><se_high>Carrie: OW! Ow, ow, ow!

<voice_0x01001179><se_high>Carrie: What's UP with this door?
It's all hot! I'm SO going to get burned!

<voice_0x0100117A><se_def>Cash: Well, duh! The burn is the mark of the
family heir! Why do you think they're
called ‘Doors of Judgement’?

<voice_0x0100117B><se_def>Cash: If you can't stand the heat,
get out of the kitchen!

<voice_0x0100117C><se_high>Carrie: Wait, so I have to open BOTH of these doors?
I can barely get the one open.
It's impossible to do alone.

<voice_0x0100117D><se_high>Carrie: Whatever.
Guess there's only one thing to do.

<voice_0x0100117E><se_high>Carrie: If you feel sorry about that dirty trick you pulled, now's your chance to make up for it.
Help me open the doors.

<voice_0x0100117F><se_high>Carrie: If you do, I'll agree to split the fortune.
That means we'll own the casino together. Deal?
<voice_0x01001180><se_def>Cash: You won't hear me complaining. But don't come crying to me if you start regretting it later.

<voice_0x01001181><se_high>Carrie: Come on.
That side's all yours.
<voice_0x01001182><se_def>Cash: Let's do it.

<voice_0x01001183><se_high>Carrie: AAAAAAHHH!!!
OW, OW, OW!

<voice_0x01001184><se_def>Cash: What are you crying about?
This is nothing compared to getting smacked upside the head by a monster!
<voice_0x01001185><se_high>Carrie: I'm not crying! I just want to get back home and put some ice on my hand!
<voice_0x01001186><se_def>Cash: Not until after we go in and have our audience with our ancestor!

<voice_0x01001187><se_high>Carrie: Bodyguards! You'd better come too.
We're not done here yet.
